{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01XQM5MeH5kYDN7uKYgVGeE1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CockroachDB cluster is deployed and fully operational.\n\n## Summary\n\nA 3-node CockroachDB cluster is running in the `cockroachdb` namespace, using only native Kubernetes resources (no operator, no CRDs) and the pre-existing RBAC (`crdb-cluster-sa`).\n\n**Resources created:**\n- **Headless Service** `crdb-cluster` (`clusterIP: None`) — exposes `grpc` (26257) and `http` (8080); provides stable per-pod DNS.\n- **Public Service** `crdb-cluster-public` (ClusterIP) — same ports, for client access.\n- **StatefulSet** `crdb-cluster` — 3 replicas, image `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0`, insecure mode.\n- **PodDisruptionBudget** `crdb-cluster` (`maxUnavailable: 1`) — guarantees quorum (≥2 of 3 nodes) survives voluntary disruptions.\n\n**Key configuration details:**\n- Each pod advertises itself by its stable DNS name (`$(hostname).crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`).\n- `--join` lists all 3 node DNS names so any pod can bootstrap into the cluster.\n- VolumeClaimTemplate `datadir` → 3× 10Gi PVCs, all `Bound`.\n- Ran `cockroach init` once to bootstrap the cluster (required with `--join`).\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- StatefulSet `3/3` ready; all 3 pods `1/1 Running`.\n- All 3 PVCs `Bound` at 10Gi.\n- `cockroach node status` confirms 3 nodes, all live and available.\n- PDB shows `ALLOWED DISRUPTIONS: 1`, preserving quorum.\n\nThe manifest is saved at `crdb.yaml` in the stage directory."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1127,"cache_read_input_tokens":31785,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1127},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a093e5a8-58cd-4094-a64